[[span style="font-family:cavolini"]]"I'm glad you're enjoying yourself. I feel a little nauseous personally. Type blues."[[/span]] Sherry grumbled, setting her feet slightly apart and moving her hand away from her side arm.

The stage before them shook and rapidly began to sink, taking the orchestra pit and choir down with it as nearly everything vanished beneath the waves.[[footnote]][[span style="color:green"]]//It's important to note at this point that certain instruments remained visible, mostly Tuba bells and bassoons. Have fun with that mental image.//[[/span]][[/footnote]]^^,^^[[footnote]][[span style="color:green"]]//The Choir and Orchestra were also completely unbothered by the fact that they were suddenly submerged in an ocean. It's almost like they weren't even aware!//[[/span]][[/footnote]]

